KillSwitchStatus

Kill switch status information for monitoring. Provides visibility into kill switch state and activation history.

type KillSwitchStatus {
  enabled: Boolean!
  mode: KillSwitchMode!
  active: Boolean!
  lastActivatedAt: DateTime
  lastDeactivatedAt: DateTime
  fallbackInterfaceID: String
  activationCount: Int!
  lastActivationReason: String
}

Fields

KillSwitchStatus.enabledBoolean! non-null scalar

Whether kill switch is enabled

KillSwitchStatus.modeKillSwitchMode! non-null enum

Kill switch behavior mode

KillSwitchStatus.activeBoolean! non-null scalar

Whether kill switch is currently active (blocking traffic)

KillSwitchStatus.lastActivatedAtDateTime scalar

Timestamp when kill switch was last activated

KillSwitchStatus.lastDeactivatedAtDateTime scalar

Timestamp when kill switch was last deactivated

KillSwitchStatus.fallbackInterfaceIDString scalar

Fallback interface ID (if mode=FALLBACK_SERVICE)

KillSwitchStatus.activationCountInt! non-null scalar

Number of times kill switch has been activated

KillSwitchStatus.lastActivationReasonString scalar

Reason for most recent activation (service_down, health_check_failed, etc.)

Returned By

killSwitchStatus query

ISPInfo
